                      <p class="medium">Welcome to Ask SFPC: Sex Ed, a peer-to-peer sex advice column that intends to distribute the production of knowledge around sex by inviting us to learn about sex from a network of our peers and friends.
                        This is a diversion from some of our previous experiences with sex advice columns, which often privilege the production of knowledge around sex to singular voices of authority.

                      </p>

                      <p class="small">
                        <!-- <span class="caption"> -->

                            “Peer-to-peer (P2P) computing or networking is a distributed application architecture that partitions tasks or workloads between peers. Peers are equally privileged, equipotent participants in the application. They are said to form a peer-to-peer network of nodes.”

                        <!-- </span> -->
                      </p>

                      <a href="https://www.are.na/block/689455">
                        <img class="margin-top" src="https://d2w9rnfcy7mm78.cloudfront.net/689455/original_dd5fd9f96c99bbfd7f71cef16952a792.jpg">
                      </a>

                      <BR><BR>
                        <p class="small">
                          This collaborative project is a living archive for the Summer 2022 program, SFPC: Sex Ed, at the School for Poetic Computation.
                          We asked applicants, teachers and special guests to respond to the following:
                        </p>


                      <!-- <div class="submission-info">
